# VGER NOTES

## To run vger without a docker container:

* add 'scred' system user

  useradd -d /home/vger -mr scred

* start a bash shell for scred

  /usr/bin/sudo -u scred bash
  cd /home/vger

In the /home/vger directory, using scred's shell, do the following:

* get miniconda installer and install miniconda into /home/vger/m2

  bash Miniconda2-latest-Linux-x86_64.sh

* conda install postgresql

  ./m2/bin/conda install postgresql

* create directory for postgresql database:

  ./m2/bin/pg_ctl init -D /home/vger/vgerdb

* start postgresql

  /usr/bin/sudo -u scred pg_ctl -D /home/vger/vgerdb -l /home/vger/vgerdb_log start

* create database

  /usr/bin/sudo -u scred createdb [-w] vgerdb

  (use -w option for "no password")

* install pangalactic.vger

  ./m2/bin/conda install [-c channel] pangalactic.vger

* set appropriate configuration options

  ...

* start vger:

  ...

